OL,4,Ckeeping an island language alive
OL,6,FAlentou d' St Helyi, y'a des
OL,7,F'Wayfinder', des singnes auvec eune
OL,8,Fcarte de la Ville et d's informations
OL,9,Fentouor le quartchi.
OL,11,FFor those not fluent in Jersey's
OL,12,Fnative language of Jerriais, it is
OL,13,Fhoped new 'talking signs' in St Helier
OL,14,Fwill help residents and visitors
OL,15,Funderstand and more easily listen to
OL,16,Fthe traditional dialect.
OL,18,FThe above statement reads: "Around St
OL,19,FHelier, there are 'Wayfinder signs'
OL,20,Fwith a map of the town and information
OL,21,Fabout the area."
