OL,3,CFind out how 'talking signs' are
OL,4,Ckeeping an island language alive
OL,6,FThe information boards have been
OL,7,Fplaced at 15 historic landmarks in the
OL,8,Ftown.
OL,10,FEach has a QR code that, once scanned,
OL,11,Freads snippets of St Helier's history
OL,12,Fin Jerriais with a translation
OL,13,Fprovided in English.
OL,15,FMature students learning with L'Office
OL,16,Fdu Jerriais, who teach the language in
OL,17,Fschools and online, devised the
OL,18,Fproject.
OL,20,FLaurence Curtis says the original idea
OL,21,Fcame from tourists.
